author: Sara Schonhardt
title: Status Quo Tests Indonesia’s ‘Outsider’ Leader
text:
JAKARTA—During his presidential campaign last year, Joko Widodo was buoyed by his image as a graft-free political outsider who would fight for the needs of ordinary people.
When he captured the Indonesian presidency, the 54-year-old former furniture salesman became the first Indonesian leader to hail from beyond the political and military elite... To Read the Full Story, Subscribe or Sign In
